The paper deals with the problem of set similarity search, which is a fundamental problem in data management and has applications in data cleaning. The paper focuses on identifying vectors with large Pearson correlation, but the results extend to other similarity measures. The paper proposes an indexing data structure that is a recursive, data-dependent partitioning of vectors inspired by recent advances in set similarity search. The paper also analyzes the set similarity problem under a random data model that reflects the kind of skewed data distributions seen in practice. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DB (Databases), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
